Package com.rubynaxela.teaeditor.datatypes.database

Classes of the database objects

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Identifiable
    The Identifiable interface is used to group database objects (which all have an ID)
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractPrimaryElement
    The AbstractPrimaryElement class is the base class for elements that have an ID, a name and a color
    Brand
    The Brand class is used to store brands from database.
    BrewingInstruction
    The BrewingInstruction class is used to store data about tea brewing recipe
    Shelf
    The Shelf class is used to store shelves from database.
    TeaBox
    The TeaBox class is used to store tea boxes from database.
    TeaData
    The TeaData class is used to store the entire database as one object imported from a JSON file
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AbstractPrimaryElement.Parameter  
    TeaBox.Parameter
